===== Image analysis =====

  * **[[http://www.bioss.ac.uk/staff/chris.html|Image Analysis for the Biological Sciences (online)]]**\\ An excellent book on Image Analysis applied to Biological Sciences: 'Image Analysis for the Biological Sciences' - Glasbey, C.A. and Horgan, G.W. (published by Wiley in 1995, but now out of press)
  * **[[http://www.efg2.com/Lab/|efg's Computer Lab]]**\\ Image Processing, Color, Graphics, Fractals
  * **[[http://www.ph.tn.tudelft.nl/Courses/FIP/frames/fip.html|**Image Processing fundamentals]]**\\ A tutorial from Delft University of Technology.
  * **[[http://homepages.inf.ed.ac.uk/rbf/HIPR2/|Hypermedia Image Processing Reference]]**\\ An Image Processing reference from the Department of Artificial Intelligence in the University of Edinburgh.
  * **[[http://www.reindeergraphics.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=196&amp;Itemid=120|Image Analysis Cookboook]]**\\ An online resource with lots of imaging examples, by Reindeer Graphics.
  * **[[http://homepages.inf.ed.ac.uk/rbf/CVonline/books.htm|Computer Vision books]]**\\ A collection of online books on Computer Vision (and related subjects).
  * **[[http://www.archive.org/details/Lectures_on_Image_Processing|Lectures on Image Processing ]]**\\ Lectures on Image Processing: A collection of 18 lectures in pdf format from Alan Peters at Vanderbilt University. 

  * **[[http://mdigest.jrc.ec.europa.eu/|Morphology Digest ]]**\\ The Morphology Digest list provides a communication channel between people interested in mathematical morphology and morphological image analysis.

===== Spectral imaging =====

  * **[[http://www.mcb.arizona.edu/ipc/fret/| Fluorescent Spectra Interactive Database ]]**\\ An excellent interactive site to combine and compare any and all combinations of fluorescent molecules, filters, mirrors and excitation sources.
  * **[[http://home.earthlink.net/~pubspectra/|PubSpectra]]**\\ PubSpectra has links to files containing dye/protein, filters and light sources/other spectra. The non-spectral section contains links and information on over 5000 dyes, over 1000 fluorescent proteins and specifications on hundreds of objective lenses.

===== Test images =====

  * **[[http://sipi.usc.edu/database/|The USC-SIPI Image Database ]]**\\ A number of test images and sequences.
  * **[[http://www.ux.uis.no/~tranden/brodatz.html| Brodatz textures ]]**\\ A collection of textured images.
  * **[[http://www.wotsit.org/|Graphic Image formats ]]**\\ A programmer's file and data format resource. The site contains information on hundreds of different file types, data types, hardware interface details and other useful programming information; algorithms, source code, specifications, etc.

